Introduction¶

This dataset collects information from 100k medical appointments in Brazil and is focused on the question of whether or not patients show up for their appointment. A number of characteristics about the patient are included in each row.

The features are:

1)PatientId:it represent the patient ID

2)AppointmentID:it represent appointement ID

3)Gender:it represent the sex of person which is (Male or Female)

4)ScheduledDay:which represent scaduale time and date

5)AppointmentDay:which represent appointment time and date and it should be after scadualeday

6)Age:represent the age of patient

7)Neighbourhood:represent hospital location

8)Scholarship: indicates whether or not the patient is enrolled in Brasilian welfare program

9)Hipertension:it represent whether or not the patient has hypertinsion disease

10)Diabetes:it represent whether or not the patient has diabatic disease or not

11)Alcoholism:it represent whether or not drink alcohol

12)Handcap:indicate whether or not patient are sick or no

13)SMS_received:represent wheather or not the patient recive an sms

14)No-show:it says No if the patient showed up to their appointment, and Yes if they did not show up.

So let's try make some enhancement to avoid this false insights¶

this defined function take series data and get it's recoplical of each to make some enhancement of our insights in case of male and female the data is biased toword female so we get factor we can multiply on rersults to get better insight and reduced biased

In [41]:
def get_enhance(data):
    for i in data.index:
        data[i]=np.reciprocal(data[i])
    data.rename(index=lambda x:x+'_enhance',inplace=True)
    return data
